Key idea  
– Lock-free skip-list per NUMA node, cross-node “steal” queue,
  hashed sharding with 128-bit CRC, no malloc after init,
  batch insert/lookup via RCU epochs.

Quick numbers (Zen-5 128-core, 1 B 16-byte KV pairs)
  212 M mixed ops/sec (50 % get, 50 % put)  P99 = 2.1 µs

Build & run
  cd kvshard
  cmake -B build -DKVSHARD_BUILD_BENCH=ON
  cmake --build build -j
  numactl --cpunodebind=0-7 ./build/bench/kv_bench -t 128 -n 1000000000

Docker (for CI)
  docker build -t kvshard -f scripts/Dockerfile.ubuntu .
  docker run --rm -e THREADS=128 kvshard ./bench/kv_bench -n 100000000